FBIS3-28525 "dreas026_n_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-026 Document Type:Daily Report 8 Feb 1994 Vietnam Remains of 13 U.S. Servicemen Returned BK0802150894 Hanoi VNA in English 1454 GMT 8 Feb 94 BK0802150894 Hanoi VNA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Hanoi VNA Feb. 8 -- The Vietnam MIA office yesterday handed over to the representatives of the US military Joint Task Force on the MIA issue 13 remains of the American servicemen and personal effects relating to 26 American militarymen reported missing in the Vietnam war. It is the first handover since US President Bill Clinton's decision to lift the trade embargo on Vietnam last week. And since March 1974, Vietnam has on 46 occasions returned the remains of 593 American servicemen to the US side. Of the 13 remains returned yesterday, six were collected by the Vietnam-US joint search teams during the 27th joint search operation for MIAs and seven handed over by the local people. The US side appreciated the humanitarian policy and cooperation of the Vietnamese Government and people in settling the MIA issue.
